<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,842,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1682,1708]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[385,435,1682,1708]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[770,837,1682,1708]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Japan</collectingCountry>
and is deposited in the Natural History Museum, London. 
<bibRefCitation author="Caradja" box="[258,595,1722,1748]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" refString="Caradja, A. &amp; Meyrick, E. (1935) Materialien zu einer Microlepidopteren - Fauna der chinesischen Provinzen Kiangsu, Chekiang und Hunan. Berlin R. Friedlahnder &amp; Soln, 45 - 47." type="book chapter" year="1935">
Caradja and Meyrick (
<number box="[525,586,1722,1748]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="1935.0">1935</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported the distribution of the species in Shanghai, 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1293,1722,1748]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time. Then 
<bibRefCitation author="Shen" box="[285,548,1762,1788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" refString="Shen, G. P. &amp; Chen, X. Y. (1995) The species and distribution of Pterophoridae in Shanghai and Jiangxi. Acta Agriculturae Universitatia Jiangxiensis, 17 (4), 419 - 426. (In Chinese)" type="journal article" year="1995">
Shen and Chen (
<number box="[478,539,1762,1788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded its distribution in Tonggu, Jiangxi Province. But the female is still unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,842,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">According to previous records, the valvae of this species are nearly symmetrical. During our research, we found some variation. The specimen from Hebei Province has nearly symmetrical valvae, but the specimens from Henan Province have obvious distinctions: the left valva is wide and short, while the right valva is slightly narrower and longer. In addition, the specimens from Henan Province are larger than the specimen from Hebei Province.</paragraph>
